author: Erica Gonzales
title: Hillary Clinton and Her Saturday Night Live Impersonator Kate McKinnon Had Dinner Together
text:
Donald Trump called Alec Baldwin's impressions of him "mean-spirited and not very good," and Sean Spicer said Melissa McCarthy "needs to slow down on the gum chewing," but Hillary Clinton and her impersonator, Kate McKinnon, now go on dinner dates. The two were spotted dining together at Orso in New York City, according to Page Six . They were reportedly accompanied by Sarah Schneider, a head writer at Saturday Night Live . Onlookers at the restaurant told the site that "lots of laughter emanated from their table."
